AUDIO: 'Have you ever wished you could capture realistic 3D movement without using one of those expensive motion capture suits? Like imagine shooting a normal video on your phone, uploading it to a website, and in just a few minutes getting a full 3D animation file ready for Blender,'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Unreal Engine, or even Mixmo. No studio, no sensors, just AI. Well, that\'s exactly what today\'s tool claims to do. It\'s called Quick Magic. And over the past few weeks, it\'s been popping up all'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'over animator and 3D artist communities. People are calling it the lazy person\'s mocap system. And honestly, I had to find out if that\'s true. So, in this video, we\'re going to test QuickMagic, break down how it works, see what it'

[00:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'gets right. Quick Magic is an AI motion capture platform. Basically, it takes an ordinary 2D video, a clip of you dancing, walking, acting, or doing anything with full body motion, and'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
